{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ef8f7de9-86c4-49d0-9e03-2f9c02728803","content":"I can help guide you on analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**Using LLDB (Linux)**:\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load /usr/share/dotnet/shared/Microsoft.NETCore.App/<version>/libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg (Windows)**:\nLoad the dump, then use SOS commands (`!analyze -v`, `!clrstack`, `!pe`).\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on the file if it's accessible in this environment? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"685808c9-2b23-4a88-b3a0-ae89cf2d4b0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":394,"requestId":"CB13:E9D27:1EE2DA6:2236358:6A052B22"},"id":"2d047600-3495-41d5-ae9a-daf13b5b19e4","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:53:49.401Z","parentId":"ed1ba64f-e876-46b4-a351-084b405cfbe8"}
